text=! Software Raid's%0aBuilding a RAID1 (boot) / RAID5 (root) with ASUS P5GDC-V Deluxe\\%0aFor the fast and furious:%0a!!!tools:%0a* mdadm%0a* jfsutils%0a!!!Most important steps for /dev/md0%0a# Install Lilo 22.6%0a# mknod /dev/md0 b 9 0%0a# mdadm -Cv /dev/md0 -l1 -n4 -c128 missing /dev/sdb1 /dev/sdc1 /dev/sdd1%0a# mkfs.jfs /dev/md0%0a# umount /boot%0a# mdadm -a /dev/md0 /dev/sda1 -> (4 disks=[UUUU], only possible if /boot not mounted)%0a# mkdir /mnt/newroot%0a# mknod /dev/md1 b 9 1%0a# mount /dev/md1 /mnt/newroot (do not yet hot-add the 4th disk!)%0a# mkdir /mnt/newroot/boot%0a# mount /dev/md0 /mnt/newroot/boot%0a# find . -xdev | cpio -pm /mnt/newroot (do not use: cp -ax / /mnt/newroot!!)%0a# fdisk /dev/sda and make /dev/sda1 and /dev/sda3 "fd"%0a# mount -o bind /dev /mnt/newroot/dev/%0a# mount -o bind /proc /mnt/newroot/proc/%0a# chroot /mnt/newroot /bin/bash/%0a# Edit lilo.conf so boot = /dev/md0%0a# Lilo -x mbr (Thanks John!!)%0a# Edit /etc/fstab%0a# The End: Do not forget to 'fd' /dev/sda1 and /dev/sda3%0a# If you can not mount /dev/md0 redo mkfs.jfs.%0a# Do not forget: To mdadm -a you must boot on md1.%0a# And: Do not forget to create the initial console when you are chrooted in /mnt/newroot:%0a%0aTo see which devices nodes are present before the /dev filesystem is mounted, run the following commands:%0a%0a# mkdir test   %0a# mount --bind / test   %0a# cd test/dev   %0a# ls%0a%0a%0aThe devices needed for a successful boot are /dev/null and /dev/console. If they didn't show up in the previous test, you have to create them manually. Issue the following commands in the test/dev/ directory:%0a%0a# mknod -m 660 console c 5 1   %0a# mknod -m 660 null c 1 3%0a%0aWhen you're finished, don't forget to unmount the test/ directory:%0a%0a# cd ../..   %0a# umount test   %0a# rmdir test%0a%0a* [[http://gentoo.linuxhowtos.org/Misc/udev%2520guide.htm | Gentoo udev Guide]]%0a%0a* [[http://www.tldp.org/HOWTO/Software-RAID-HOWTO.html | Software Raid Howto]]%0a* [[http://www.intel.com/go/serverconfigurator | Intel Server Configurator]]%0a%0a!!! Speed Settings for Syncing%0a* /proc/sys/dev/raid/speed_limit_min%0a* echo 50000 >/proc/sys/dev/raid/speed_limit_min%0a%0a!!!When having Lilo problems%0a# boot from CD%0a# mknod /dev/md0 b 9 0%0a# mknod /dev/md1 b 9 1%0a# mdadm --assemble --run /dev/md0 /dev/hda1%0a# mdadm -a /dev/md0 /dev/hdc1%0a# mount /dev/md1 /mnt/gentoo%0a# mount /dev/md0 /mnt/gentoo/boot%0a# mount -o bind /dev /mnt/gentoo/dev%0a# mount -o bind /proc /mnt/gentoo/proc%0a# lilo -x mbr%0a%0a!!!Growing a Software Raid1%0a#  mdadm --grow /dev/md1 --size=max - also see http://www.silfreed.net/content/argo-hard-drive-upgrade-growing-raid1-array%0a# Resizing with JFS: # mount -o remount,resize /mount/point - also see http://www.linux.com/articles/32002
time=1238869733
author:1238869733=
diff:1238869733:1238869687:=59a60,70%0a> !!! Console Error%0a> ... Gentoo braucht ein /dev/console Device _bevor_ udev geladen werden kann.%0a> * > mount / -o bind /mnt%0a> %0a> ... und dann die zwei Devices console und null erstellen:%0a> * > mknod /mnt/dev/console c 5 1%0a> * > mknod /mnt/dev/null c 1 3%0a> %0a> ... und dann natürlich wieder unmounten..%0a> * > umount /mnt%0a> %0a
host:1238869733=77.58.149.99
author:1238869687=
diff:1238869687:1238857221:=30,52c30,31%0a%3c # And: Do not forget to create the initial console when you are chrooted in /mnt/newroot:%0a%3c %0a%3c To see which devices nodes are present before the /dev filesystem is mounted, run the following commands:%0a%3c %0a%3c # mkdir test   %0a%3c # mount --bind / test   %0a%3c # cd test/dev   %0a%3c # ls%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c The devices needed for a successful boot are /dev/null and /dev/console. If they didn't show up in the previous test, you have to create them manually. Issue the following commands in the test/dev/ directory:%0a%3c %0a%3c # mknod -m 660 console c 5 1   %0a%3c # mknod -m 660 null c 1 3%0a%3c %0a%3c When you're finished, don't forget to unmount the test/ directory:%0a%3c %0a%3c # cd ../..   %0a%3c # umount test   %0a%3c # rmdir test%0a%3c %0a%3c * [[http://gentoo.linuxhowtos.org/Misc/udev%2520guide.htm | Gentoo udev Guide]]%0a%3c %0a---%0a> # And: Do not forget to create the initial console!%0a> %0a
host:1238869687=77.58.149.99
author:1238857221=
diff:1238857221:1238855738:=30,31c30%0a%3c # And: Do not forget to create the initial console!%0a%3c %0a---%0a> %0a
