host:1115828900=217.162.177.109
author:1115828583=
diff:1115828583:1113920742:=8,18c8,17%0a%3c # Install Lilo 22.6%0a%3c # mknod /dev/md0 b 9 0 mknod /dev/md1 b 9 1%0a%3c # mdadm -Cv /dev/md0 -l1 -n4 -c128 missing /dev/sdb1 /dev/sdc1 /dev/sdd1%0a%3c # mdadm -a /dev/md0 /dev/sda1 -> (4 disks=[UUUU])%0a%3c # mount /dev/md1 /mnt/newroot (do not yet hot-add the 4th disk!)%0a%3c # mount /dev/md0 /mnt/newroot/boot%0a%3c # Edit lilo.conf so boot = /dev/md0%0a%3c # Lilo -x mbr (Thanks John!!)%0a%3c # The End: Do not forget to 'fd' /dev/sda1 and /dev/sda3%0a%3c # If you can not mount /dev/md0 redo mkfs.jfs.%0a%3c %0a---%0a>  1. Install Lilo 22.6%0a>  2. mdadm -Cv /dev/md0 -l1 -n4 -c128 missing /dev/sdb1 /dev/sdc1 /dev/sdd1%0a>  3. mdadm -a /dev/md0 /dev/sda1 -> (4 disks=[UUUU])%0a>  4. mount /dev/md1 /mnt/newroot (do not yet hot-add the 4th disk!)%0a>  5. mount /dev/md0 /mnt/newroot/boot%0a>  6. Edit lilo.conf so boot = /dev/md0%0a>  7. Lilo -x mbr (Thanks John!!)%0a>  8. The End: Do not forget to 'fd' /dev/sda1 and /dev/sda3%0a>  9. If you can not mount /dev/md0 redo mkfs.jfs.%0a> %0a
host:1115828583=217.162.177.109
